Hi all,

Using the matlab version (http://site.physics.georgetown.edu/matlab/tutorial.html) with the following lines we get positions of both small and large particles with no apparent pixel biasing, but in the image attached, trackpy's locate function with similar input parameters has lots of pixel biasing.

```matlab
a = double(imread('00000.tif'));
b = bpass(a,1,9);
pk = pkfnd(b,5,9);
cnt = cntrd(b,pk,11);
```

I've tried varying the parameters including percentile and minmass, but I either end up missing many of the small particles or making the bias worse. I'm not familiar enough yet with the implementation details to know why this difference might show up, so hope someone here is.

[00000.tif.zip](https://github.com/soft-matter/trackpy/files/322495/00000.tif.zip)
(github doesn't support tif files :-/)

